main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects reported at Camp Irwin, California between February 2 and February 21, 1956.
interesting points: Witnesses reported flying objects moving at extremely high speeds, one estimated at over 1,000 mph and another at over 2,000 mph., The objects were observed at high altitudes, with one sighting at 15,000 feet and others at 30,000 feet., Different types of observations were made including ground-visual and radar tracking., The sightings were confirmed by multiple military personnel, indicating reliability., The investigations faced delays causing insufficient data for conclusive analysis.
witness description: Soldiers from various military units, including PFC Richard L. Walker and others.
